Seven people have died and 15 others sustained injuries after a minibus taxi rolled down an embankment. DURBAN - Seven people have died and 15 others sustained injuries after a minibus taxi rolled down an embankment. The accident took place along the R102 in the north of Durban. Arrive Alive said in a statement that three passengers sustained critical injuries. READ: Almost 600 deaths on SA roads this festive season One of the injured had to be airlifted to hospital. KwaZulu-Natal Transport MEC Bheki Ntuli conveyed his condolences to the families of the deceased. "This tragedy, in my view, as the MEC responsible it pains me," he said. Police are probing the cause of the accident.